            <h2>Why are customers canceling their memberships?
            </h2>
            <p>Whish I knew :). But we can analyze engagement & retention metrics, feedback from users and base product decisions on them. For example, performing cohort analysis, divide customers in segments based on their “time to cancel” (i.e. cancelled after 30 days vs. canceled after more than 30 days) and focus on long-term users who have greater CLV and cancellation reasons we can address. Or we can go with churn models, calculating each customer 'Probability alive'.</p>
